The paper focuses on object proposal generation, which is a common task in computer vision and image processing. The approach is based on hierarchical segmentation and uses a submodular objective function to select the most representative and diverse object proposals. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as diversity ranking and submodular optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach can be applied to various types of images, including multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), which further support these sub-categories as likely options.
